VALUES
(49, 1, 1, 51, 1, 2, 2, 'the saints which are at Ephesus', 'Connection of Saints and Faithful', 'Both passages emphasize ''saints'' and ''faithful'' in their greetings, highlighting a shared audience of believers. This connection underscores the communal aspect of faith in Christ Jesus.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 1, 47, 1, 1, 1, 'an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God', 'Connection of Apostolic Authority', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s role as ''an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God.'' This connection highlights the authority and mission given to Paul in his letters to different churches.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 1, 46, 1, 1, 2, 'apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God', 'Connection of Apostolic Authority', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s role as an apostle of Jesus Christ by the will of God. They also address communities of believers, highlighting the concept of sanctification and being called to be saints.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 1, 45, 1, 1, 1, 'apostle of Jesus Christ', 'Paul''s Apostolic Identity', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s role as an apostle of Jesus Christ. They highlight his divine calling and mission, linking his authority and purpose in spreading the gospel.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 1, 48, 1, 1, 1, 'an apostle', 'Connection of Apostolic Authority', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s role as an apostle, highlighting his divine commissioning. The phrase ''an apostle'' in both texts underscores the authority he claims in his ministry.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 1, 45, 1, 7, 7, 'saints', 'Connection of Saints in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''saints'' as a designation for believers. Ephesians addresses ''the saints which are at Ephesus,'' while Romans refers to ''called to be saints,'' highlighting a shared identity among Christians.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 1, 66, 2, 10, 10, 'the faithful in Christ Jesus', 'Faithfulness in Suffering', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of being faithful in the face of trials. Ephesians addresses the faithful in Christ Jesus, while Revelation encourages faithfulness unto death amidst suffering.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 2, 45, 1, 7, 7, NULL, 'Connection of Grace and Peace', 'Both passages emphasize the greeting of grace and peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ. This connection highlights a shared theme of divine blessing in the introductions of both letters.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 2, 48, 1, 3, 3, 'grace be to you, and peace', 'Connection of Grace and Peace', 'Both passages emphasize ''grace'' and ''peace'' from God the Father and Jesus Christ. This connection highlights a shared greeting structure in Pauline letters.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 2, 56, 1, 4, 4, NULL, 'Connection of Grace and Peace', 'Both passages emphasize grace and peace as blessings from God the Father and Jesus Christ. This connection highlights a common theme of divine favor and well-being in the greetings of the letters.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 2, 47, 1, 2, 2, NULL, 'Shared Greeting Structure', 'Both passages emphasize a similar greeting structure, specifically invoking grace and peace from God the Father and Jesus Christ. This connection highlights the consistency in apostolic greetings across different letters.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 3, 60, 1, 3, 3, 'God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ', 'Blessings and Hope in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the role of God as the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ and highlight the blessings believers receive through Him. Ephesians speaks of spiritual blessings, while 1 Peter focuses on the hope given through Christ''s resurrection.', 'theme', 0.8739999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 3, 47, 1, 3, 3, 'Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ', 'Blessings from God', 'Both passages emphasize the blessing from God, specifically referring to Him as the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ. This connection highlights the theme of divine blessings and comfort provided to believers.', 'theme', 0.706, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 3, 49, 2, 6, 6, 'heavenly places in Christ', 'Spiritual Blessings and Heavenly Places', 'This connection highlights the theme of being blessed with spiritual blessings and the shared experience of sitting in heavenly places. Both passages emphasize the relationship believers have in Christ, linking spiritual blessings to their elevated position.', 'theme', 0.692, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 3, 1, 22, 18, 18, 'blessed us with all spiritual blessings', 'Blessings Through Obedience', 'This connection highlights the theme of blessings in both passages. Ephesians speaks of being blessed with spiritual blessings, while Genesis emphasizes that nations will be blessed through obedience.', 'theme', 0.538, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 3, 66, 5, 9, 14, 'blessed us with all spiritual blessings', 'Spiritual Blessings and Redemption', 'Both passages emphasize the blessings and redemptive work of Christ. Ephesians speaks of being blessed with spiritual blessings in Christ, while Revelation highlights the worthiness of the Lamb who redeems and makes believers kings and priests.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 3, 43, 10, 29, 30, 'blessed us with all spiritual blessings', 'Spiritual Blessings and Divine Unity', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the blessings from God and the unity of Jesus with the Father. Both passages emphasize the divine authority and security found in the Father, suggesting a deep spiritual bond.', 'theme', 0.496, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 3, 49, 1, 20, 20, 'heavenly places', 'Spiritual Blessings and Resurrection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''heavenly places'' and the blessings associated with Christ. The first verse speaks of spiritual blessings in these heavenly realms, while the second verse describes Christ''s exaltation in the same context.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 4, 55, 1, 9, 9, 'before the foundation of the world', 'Divine Purpose Before Creation', 'Both passages emphasize God''s purpose and grace given before the world began. They highlight the idea of being chosen and called according to His plan, underscoring a divine initiative that predates creation.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 4, 45, 8, 28, 30, 'chosen us in him before the foundation of the world', 'Chosen and Called Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being chosen and called by God. Ephesians speaks of being chosen ''before the foundation of the world,'' while Romans discusses those who are ''called according to his purpose.''', 'theme', 0.867, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 4, 49, 2, 10, 10, 'chosen us in him before the foundation of the world', 'Chosen for Good Works', 'This connection highlights the theme of being chosen and created for a purpose. Both passages emphasize that believers are set apart to live in holiness and engage in good works, reflecting God''s prior intentions.', 'theme', 0.7829999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 4, 40, 25, 34, 34, 'before the foundation of the world', 'Foundation of the World Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being chosen or prepared before the foundation of the world. Ephesians highlights being chosen for holiness, while Matthew speaks of inheriting a kingdom prepared from the same foundational time.', 'theme', 0.699, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 4, 59, 2, 5, 5, 'chosen us in him before the foundation of the world', 'Divine Choice and Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s choice in both passages. Ephesians emphasizes being chosen before the foundation of the world, while James speaks of God choosing the poor who are rich in faith.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 4, 60, 2, 9, 9, 'chosen us in him', 'Chosen People Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''chosen'' by God, highlighting the identity of believers as a distinct group set apart for holiness and purpose. This connection illustrates the continuity of God''s intention for His people throughout scripture.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 4, 43, 15, 16, 16, 'chosen us in him before the foundation of the world', 'Chosen by God', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine selection, as both passages emphasize that believers are chosen by God. Ephesians speaks of being chosen ''before the foundation of the world,'' while John states, ''Ye have not chosen me, but I have chosen you.''', 'theme', 0.552, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 5, 45, 8, 29, 30, 'predestinated us unto the adoption', 'Predestination and Adoption Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of predestination, linking believers'' adoption as children of God to their conformity to the image of Christ. This connection highlights the continuity of God''s plan for salvation and transformation.', 'theme', 0.622, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 5, 49, 1, 11, 11, NULL, 'Predestination and Inheritance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize predestination in relation to God''s will. Ephesians 1:5 discusses being predestinated for adoption, while Ephesians 1:11 connects predestination to obtaining an inheritance.', 'theme', 0.538, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 5, 48, 4, 5, 6, 'adoption of children', 'Adoption as Children of God', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''adoption'' into God''s family. Ephesians speaks of being predestinated for adoption, while Galatians highlights receiving the adoption of sons through redemption.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 5, 43, 1, 12, 12, 'adoption of children', 'Adoption as Children of God', 'This connection highlights the theme of becoming children of God through faith. Ephesians speaks of predestination for adoption, while John emphasizes the power given to those who believe to become sons of God.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 5, 62, 3, 1, 1, 'adoption of children by Jesus Christ', 'Adoption as Sons of God', 'This connection highlights the theme of believers being adopted as children of God. Both passages emphasize the relationship between God and His followers, portraying them as sons through His love and will.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 5, 45, 8, 14, 17, 'adoption of children by Jesus Christ', 'Adoption as Children of God', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of adoption, highlighting believers'' status as children of God. Ephesians speaks of being predestinated for adoption, while Romans describes receiving the Spirit of adoption.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 5, 48, 3, 26, 26, 'adoption of children by Jesus Christ', 'Children of God Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''children of God.'' Ephesians highlights predestination for adoption through Christ, while Galatians states that faith in Christ makes one a child of God.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 6, 45, 3, 22, 26, 'the glory of his grace', 'Grace and Justification Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of grace in salvation. Ephesians highlights being accepted in the beloved, while Romans discusses being justified freely by his grace. This connection highlights the central theme of grace in the believer''s relationship with God.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 6, 49, 1, 12, 12, NULL, 'Praise of His Glory', 'Both passages emphasize being to the praise of his glory. Ephesians 1:6 highlights being accepted in the beloved, which relates to the trust in Christ mentioned in Ephesians 1:12.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 6, 51, 1, 13, 13, 'accepted in the beloved', 'Grace and Deliverance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the transformative power of God''s grace. Ephesians speaks of being accepted in the beloved, while Colossians highlights deliverance from darkness into the kingdom of the Son.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 6, 50, 4, 19, 19, 'the glory of his grace', 'Grace and Supply Connection', 'Both passages emphasize God''s provision and grace. Ephesians highlights being accepted in the beloved, while Philippians assures that God will supply needs according to his riches in glory.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 6, 40, 3, 17, 17, 'in the beloved', 'Beloved Connection in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''beloved.'' Ephesians speaks of being accepted in the beloved, while Matthew identifies Jesus as the beloved Son, highlighting a shared theme of divine acceptance and favor.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 6, 50, 1, 11, 11, NULL, 'Connection of Glory and Praise', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of glory and praise directed towards God. Ephesians highlights being accepted in the beloved to the praise of His grace, while Philippians speaks of being filled with righteousness unto the glory and praise of God.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 6, 60, 2, 9, 9, NULL, 'Connection of Praise and Acceptance', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of praising God for His grace and calling. Ephesians highlights being accepted in the beloved, while 1 Peter speaks of showing forth the praises of Him who calls us into light.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 7, 60, 2, 24, 24, 'redemption through his blood', 'Redemption and Healing Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of redemption and healing through Christ''s sacrifice. Ephesians speaks of redemption through his blood, while 1 Peter highlights bearing our sins and healing by his stripes.', 'theme', 0.776, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 7, 45, 3, 24, 24, 'redemption through his blood', 'Redemption and Grace Connection', 'Both passages emphasize redemption through grace. Ephesians highlights redemption through his blood, while Romans speaks of justification freely by his grace through redemption.', 'theme', 0.7409999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 7, 51, 1, 14, 14, 'redemption through his blood', 'Redemption Through His Blood', 'Both passages emphasize redemption through his blood and the forgiveness of sins. This connection highlights a shared theme of salvation and grace in Christ.', 'theme', 0.622, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 7, 62, 1, 7, 9, NULL, 'Redemption and Forgiveness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the blood of Jesus in providing forgiveness of sins. Ephesians highlights redemption through his blood, while 1 John speaks of the cleansing power of that same blood. This connection highlights the continuity of the theme of forgiveness in the New Testament.', 'theme', 0.615, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 7, 60, 1, 18, 19, 'redemption through his blood', 'Redemption through Christ''s Blood', 'Both passages emphasize redemption through the blood of Christ. Ephesians highlights the forgiveness of sins, while 1 Peter specifies the precious blood of Christ as the means of redemption.', 'theme', 0.58, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 7, 58, 9, 22, 22, 'redemption through his blood', 'Redemption and Forgiveness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of blood for redemption and forgiveness of sins. Ephesians highlights redemption through blood, while Hebrews states that without shedding of blood, there is no remission.', 'theme', 0.566, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 7, 58, 9, 12, 15, 'redemption through his blood', 'Redemption Through Christ''s Blood', 'Both passages emphasize redemption through Christ''s blood, highlighting its significance in forgiveness and eternal inheritance. Ephesians speaks of redemption and forgiveness, while Hebrews elaborates on the eternal redemption obtained through Christ''s sacrifice.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 8, 66, 5, 12, 12, 'wisdom', 'Connection of Wisdom in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize wisdom as a divine attribute. Ephesians highlights God''s abundance in wisdom, while Revelation acknowledges the Lamb''s worthiness to receive wisdom among other virtues.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 8, 45, 5, 15, 15, 'abounded toward us in all wisdom', 'Abundance of Grace and Wisdom', 'This connection highlights the theme of abundance in both passages. Ephesians speaks of wisdom and prudence abounding toward us, while Romans emphasizes grace and the gift of grace abounding unto many.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 8, 49, 3, 10, 10, 'wisdom', 'Wisdom in Ephesians', 'Both passages emphasize the ''wisdom'' of God. Ephesians 1:8 speaks of God''s wisdom abounding toward us, while Ephesians 3:10 reveals that the church makes known this manifold wisdom to heavenly powers.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 8, 51, 2, 3, 3, 'wisdom', 'Wisdom and Knowledge Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of wisdom present in both passages. Ephesians speaks of God abounding in wisdom, while Colossians emphasizes that all treasures of wisdom are found in Christ.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 8, 19, 104, 24, 24, 'wisdom', 'Wisdom in Creation and Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of wisdom. Ephesians highlights God''s wisdom given to us, while Psalms praises God''s wisdom in creation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 8, 20, 8, 12, 12, 'wisdom and prudence', 'Wisdom and Prudence Connection', 'This connection highlights the relationship between wisdom and prudence in both passages. Ephesians emphasizes God''s abundance in wisdom and prudence, while Proverbs personifies wisdom as dwelling with prudence.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 8, 23, 52, 13, 13, 'in all wisdom and prudence', 'Wisdom and Prudence Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of prudence. Ephesians highlights God''s abundance in wisdom and prudence, while Isaiah describes the servant who will deal prudently.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 9, 51, 1, 26, 28, 'mystery of his will', 'Connection of Divine Mystery', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a ''mystery'' that has been revealed to believers. Ephesians speaks of the mystery of God''s will, while Colossians elaborates on the mystery of Christ among the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 9, 45, 16, 25, 27, 'mystery of his will', 'Revelation of the Mystery', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a ''mystery'' that has been revealed. Ephesians speaks of the ''mystery of his will,'' while Romans refers to the ''revelation of the mystery'' that was kept secret. This connection highlights the unfolding of divine purpose across both texts.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 9, 49, 3, 3, 9, 'mystery of his will', 'Revelation of the Mystery', 'Both passages emphasize the revelation of a mystery related to God''s will and purpose. Ephesians 1:9 introduces the mystery of His will, while Ephesians 3:3-9 elaborates on the mystery revealed to the apostles regarding the inclusion of the Gentiles in God''s promise.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 9, 55, 1, 9, 9, NULL, 'Connection of Purpose and Grace', 'Both passages emphasize God''s purpose in salvation. Ephesians speaks of God''s will and good pleasure, while 2 Timothy highlights His purpose and grace given in Christ.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 9, 49, 1, 11, 11, 'according to his good pleasure', 'Connection of God''s Purpose', 'Both passages emphasize the ''purpose'' of God in relation to His will and the inheritance of believers. They highlight the idea that God''s plans are intentional and predestined according to His counsel.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 9, 45, 8, 28, 28, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Purpose', 'Both passages emphasize God''s purpose and will. Ephesians speaks of the mystery of His will, while Romans highlights that all things work together according to His purpose.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 9, 48, 1, 12, 12, 'mystery of his will', 'Revelation of God''s Will', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine revelation. Ephesians speaks of the ''mystery of his will,'' while Galatians emphasizes receiving knowledge ''by the revelation of Jesus Christ.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 10, 51, 1, 20, 20, 'all things in Christ, both which are in heaven, and which are on earth', 'Reconciliation of All Things', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering and reconciliation of all things in Christ, highlighting a cosmic scope that includes both heaven and earth. This connection underscores the unity and peace established through Christ''s work.', 'theme', 0.657, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 10, 50, 2, 9, 10, NULL, 'Unity in Christ''s Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of all things in Christ, highlighting his authority over heaven and earth. The mention of ''things in heaven, and things in earth'' in both verses reinforces this theme of universal submission to Christ.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 10, 48, 4, 4, 4, 'fulness of times', 'Fulness of Time Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''fulness of time,'' indicating a significant moment in God''s plan. Ephesians speaks of gathering all things in Christ, while Galatians highlights the sending of His Son at this appointed time.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 10, 27, 2, 44, 44, 'gather together in one all things in Christ', 'Kingdom Establishment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the establishment of a divine kingdom. Ephesians speaks of gathering all things in Christ, while Daniel foretells a kingdom that will never be destroyed.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 10, 41, 1, 15, 15, 'fulness of times', 'Fulfillment of Time and Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of fulfillment in relation to time and God''s plan. Ephesians speaks of the ''fulness of times'' while Mark declares ''the time is fulfilled,'' linking the idea of divine timing in God''s redemptive work.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 10, 58, 1, 2, 2, 'all things in Christ', 'Connection of Christ''s Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the gathering of all things in Christ and his role as heir of all things. This connection highlights the centrality of Christ in God''s plan for both heaven and earth.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 10, 23, 2, 2, 4, 'gather together in one all things in Christ', 'Unity in Christ and Nations', 'Both passages emphasize a future gathering of all nations and peoples under God''s authority. Ephesians speaks of gathering all things in Christ, while Isaiah envisions nations flowing to the mountain of the Lord, indicating a unified worship and peace.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 11, 45, 8, 28, 28, NULL, 'Inheritance and Purpose Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of purpose in God''s plan. Ephesians speaks of being predestinated according to God''s purpose, while Romans asserts that all things work together for good according to His purpose.', 'theme', 0.6499999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 11, 60, 1, 4, 4, 'inheritance', 'Inheritance in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of an inheritance. Ephesians speaks of obtaining an inheritance through predestination, while 1 Peter describes an inheritance that is incorruptible and reserved in heaven.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 11, 23, 46, 10, 11, 'according to the purpose of him', 'Divine Counsel and Purpose', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of God''s counsel and purpose in executing His will. Ephesians speaks of being predestinated according to God''s purpose, while Isaiah declares that His counsel shall stand and He will accomplish His plans.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 11, 49, 1, 14, 14, 'inheritance', 'Inheritance and Redemption Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''inheritance'' and its significance in the believer''s relationship with God. The first verse discusses obtaining an inheritance through predestination, while the second verse refers to the earnest of that inheritance until redemption.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 11, 49, 1, 5, 5, 'predestinated according to the purpose', 'Predestination and Inheritance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize predestination according to God''s will. Ephesians 1:5 discusses being predestinated for adoption, while Ephesians 1:11 refers to obtaining an inheritance through predestination. This connection highlights the continuity of God''s purpose in both contexts.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 11, 45, 8, 17, 17, 'we have obtained an inheritance', 'Inheritance and Heirs Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of inheritance, linking believers as heirs of God. Ephesians speaks of obtaining an inheritance, while Romans describes believers as heirs and joint-heirs with Christ.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 11, 48, 3, 18, 18, 'inheritance', 'Inheritance and Promise Connection', 'This connection highlights the concept of inheritance in both passages. Ephesians speaks of an inheritance obtained through God''s purpose, while Galatians contrasts this with the inheritance of the law, emphasizing that it was given by promise.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 12, 49, 1, 6, 6, 'to the praise of his glory', 'Praise of His Glory', 'Both passages emphasize being to the praise of his glory, highlighting the significance of God''s grace and acceptance in Christ. This connection underscores the theme of glorifying God through faith in the beloved.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
