(49, 1, 23, 46, 15, 28, 28, 'fulness of him that filleth all in all', 'Unity of God in All', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of God being ''all in all.'' Ephesians highlights the fullness of Christ''s body, while 1 Corinthians speaks of God being all in all after subjugation of all things.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 1, 23, 46, 12, 12, 27, NULL, 'Unity of the Body of Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of the body of Christ, highlighting its unity and diversity. Ephesians describes the church as the body, while 1 Corinthians elaborates on the many members that make up this one body.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 1, 51, 2, 13, 13, 'dead in trespasses and sins', 'Connection of Spiritual Resurrection', 'Both passages emphasize being ''dead in trespasses and sins'' and highlight the act of being ''quickened'' or made alive. This connection illustrates the theme of spiritual renewal through forgiveness.', 'theme', 0.923, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 1, 49, 2, 5, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Spiritual Resurrection', 'Both passages emphasize being ''dead in sins'' and the act of being ''quickened.'' This connection highlights the transition from spiritual death to life through Christ, underscoring the theme of salvation by grace.', 'theme', 0.566, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 1, 51, 3, 1, 4, 'dead in trespasses and sins', 'Connection of Spiritual Resurrection', 'Both passages emphasize the transformation from death to life in Christ. Ephesians speaks of being quickened from death in sins, while Colossians refers to being risen with Christ, highlighting a shared theme of spiritual renewal.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 1, 45, 8, 2, 2, 'dead in trespasses and sins', 'Connection of Life and Death', 'Both passages emphasize the transition from death to life. Ephesians speaks of being quickened from death in sin, while Romans highlights freedom from the law of sin and death.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 1, 49, 4, 18, 18, 'dead in trespasses and sins', 'Connection of Spiritual Death and Ignorance', 'Both passages emphasize a state of spiritual death and alienation from God. Ephesians 2:1 speaks of being ''dead in trespasses and sins,'' while Ephesians 4:18 describes being ''alienated from the life of God'' due to ignorance.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 1, 43, 5, 21, 21, 'quickened', 'Connection of Quickening Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''quickened'' from death. Ephesians speaks of being quickened from spiritual death, while John refers to the Son''s ability to quicken the dead, highlighting a shared theme of resurrection and life.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 1, 43, 11, 25, 26, 'dead in trespasses and sins', 'Connection of Life and Death', 'This connection highlights the theme of being ''dead'' and the promise of life. Ephesians speaks of being ''dead in trespasses and sins,'' while John emphasizes that belief in Jesus leads to life even after death.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 2, 49, 6, 12, 12, 'prince of the power of the air', 'Spiritual Warfare and Influence', 'Both passages emphasize the struggle against spiritual forces. Ephesians 2:2 mentions ''the prince of the power of the air,'' while Ephesians 6:12 refers to ''principalities'' and ''powers,'' highlighting the same spiritual conflict.', 'theme', 0.538, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 2, 62, 5, 19, 19, 'course of this world', 'Connection of Worldly Influence', 'Both passages emphasize the influence of wickedness in the world. Ephesians describes walking according to the ''course of this world,'' while 1 John states that ''the whole world lieth in wickedness.''', 'theme', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 2, 49, 2, 3, 3, 'children of disobedience', 'Connection of Disobedience and Wrath', 'Both passages emphasize the state of humanity prior to salvation, highlighting the influence of the ''prince of the power of the air'' and the resulting ''children of wrath.'' This connection highlights the shared theme of disobedience and its consequences.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 2, 43, 12, 31, 31, NULL, 'Connection of Worldly Influence', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a ''prince'' associated with the world. Ephesians refers to the ''prince of the power of the air,'' while John speaks of the ''prince of this world,'' indicating a shared theme of spiritual authority over worldly matters.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 2, 43, 8, 44, 44, 'prince of the power of the air', 'Connection of Spiritual Influence', 'Both passages emphasize the influence of evil. Ephesians refers to the ''prince of the power of the air,'' while John identifies the devil as a liar and murderer, highlighting a shared theme of spiritual deception and disobedience.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 2, 51, 3, 6, 7, 'children of disobedience', 'Connection of Disobedience and Wrath', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''children of disobedience'' and the consequences of walking in ways contrary to God. They highlight a shared theme of past behavior leading to divine wrath.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 2, 46, 6, 11, 11, 'children of disobedience', 'Transformation from Disobedience to Sanctification', 'This connection highlights the transition from walking ''according to the course of this world'' to being ''washed'' and ''sanctified'' in Christ. Both passages emphasize a change in identity from disobedience to a new life in the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 3, 56, 3, 3, 3, 'fulfilling the desires of the flesh', 'Connection of Human Condition', 'Both passages emphasize the sinful state of humanity, describing behaviors such as fulfilling desires and living in malice. They highlight a shared experience of disobedience and the consequences of such actions.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 3, 48, 5, 16, 24, 'fulfilling the desires of the flesh', 'Conflict Between Flesh and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the struggle between the desires of the flesh and the guidance of the Spirit. Ephesians 2:3 mentions fulfilling the desires of the flesh, while Galatians 5:16-24 contrasts these desires with the fruits of the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 3, 49, 4, 22, 22, NULL, 'Connection of Old and New Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''former conversation'' and ''lusts of the flesh.'' This connection highlights the transition from a corrupt nature to a renewed identity in Christ.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 3, 60, 1, 14, 14, 'fulfilling the desires of the flesh', 'Connection of Former Lusts', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of former lusts and desires. Ephesians discusses fulfilling the desires of the flesh, while 1 Peter instructs to not fashion yourselves according to those former lusts.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 3, 45, 13, 14, 14, 'fulfilling the desires of the flesh', 'Connection of Flesh and Desires', 'Both passages emphasize the struggle against the flesh and its desires. Ephesians discusses fulfilling the desires of the flesh, while Romans advises against making provision for the flesh.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 3, 19, 51, 5, 5, 'fulfilling the desires of the flesh', 'Connection of Sin and Nature', 'Both passages emphasize the inherent sinful nature of humanity. Ephesians speaks of fulfilling the desires of the flesh, while Psalms acknowledges being shapen in iniquity, highlighting a shared theme of sinfulness from birth.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 3, 45, 6, 12, 12, 'lusts of our flesh', 'Connection of Sin and Flesh', 'Both passages emphasize the struggle against the ''lusts'' of the flesh. Ephesians highlights past fulfillment of these desires, while Romans warns against allowing sin to reign in the body.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 4, 60, 1, 3, 3, 'rich in mercy', 'Connection of God''s Mercy', 'Both passages emphasize God''s mercy and love. Ephesians highlights God''s rich mercy, while 1 Peter speaks of abundant mercy, linking the two in their focus on divine compassion.', 'theme', 0.629, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 4, 49, 1, 7, 7, 'rich in mercy', 'Connection of Mercy and Grace', 'Both passages emphasize God''s rich mercy and grace. Ephesians 2:4 speaks of God''s mercy, while Ephesians 1:7 highlights the riches of his grace in the context of redemption and forgiveness.', 'theme', 0.538, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 4, 19, 86, 15, 15, 'rich in mercy', 'Connection of God''s Mercy', 'Both passages emphasize God''s mercy and compassion. Ephesians highlights God''s rich mercy, while Psalms describes Him as plenteous in mercy.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 4, 56, 3, 4, 7, 'rich in mercy', 'Connection of God''s Mercy and Love', 'Both passages emphasize God''s mercy and love toward humanity. Ephesians highlights God''s rich mercy and great love, while Titus elaborates on God''s kindness and love, showing how these attributes lead to salvation.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 4, 45, 5, 8, 8, 'great love wherewith he loved us', 'God''s Love and Mercy', 'Both passages emphasize God''s love for humanity, highlighting His mercy and the sacrificial act of Christ. Ephesians speaks of God''s rich mercy, while Romans illustrates this love through Christ''s death for sinners.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 4, 49, 2, 7, 7, 'rich in mercy', 'Connection of Mercy and Grace', 'Both passages emphasize God''s kindness and love toward us. The ''rich in mercy'' in Ephesians 2:4 connects to the ''exceeding riches of his grace'' in Ephesians 2:7, highlighting the theme of divine generosity.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 4, 19, 145, 8, 8, NULL, 'Connection of Mercy and Compassion', 'Both passages emphasize God''s mercy and compassion. Ephesians highlights God''s rich mercy, while Psalms describes the Lord as full of compassion and great mercy.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(49, 2, 5, 45, 3, 24, 24, 'by grace ye are saved', 'Connection of Grace and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the role of grace in salvation. Ephesians highlights being quickened with Christ, while Romans speaks of justification through grace. This connection highlights the transformative power of grace in the believer''s life.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
